  "text": "This brief survey of recent issues in CALL research indicates an increased attention to contextual, social, and cultural aspects of language learning. Thus, the field can be said to experience a process of reconstruction. Although this may be incremental, the trend towards a social (as an extension of e.g. technological or cognitive) perspective on CALL is clearly visible. But there are few, if any, studies that explicitly address sociogenesis and the relationship between individual and collective approaches, although this aspect is present in some (e.g. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Warschauer & Kern, 2000) . However, looking at the broader field of SLA, and in particular recent contributions from sociocultural perspectives, this aspect of language learning becomes more visible.",
